        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-25T15:46:16+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-25T15:46:16+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-25T05:16:16Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-25T05:16:16Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough will contract off the east coast of Victoria late Wednesday evening with a cold front set to follow on Thursday. A cold southerly airstream will establish in the wake of this front with another trough lingering in Bass Strait into Thursday evening. This trough will linger off the Gippsland coast on Friday with a low pressure system establishing in the Tasman Sea. A high pressure system will begin to slowly move in from the west on Friday, centring itself over Victoria on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
